==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sodden
<hw>Sod"den</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> [<pos>p. p.</pos> of
<er>Seethe</er>.] <def>Boiled; seethed; also, soaked; heavy with
moisture; saturated; <as>as, <ex>sodden</ex> beef; <ex>sodden</ex>
bread; <ex>sodden</ex> fields</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sodden</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sodden
<hw>Sod"den</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be seethed; to become
sodden.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sodden</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sodden
<hw>Sod"den</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To soak; to make heavy with
water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sodden-witted</ent>⟦br⟧
